data.b9665f6e-1988-11e7-83d2-6c4008b05c4c: In this analysis, the pigments in Leaf from a Gospel Book or New Testament were studied using x-ray fluorescence spectroscopy and Raman spectroscopy. The analysis indicates the use of pigments consistent with the date of the manuscript, including lead white, vermilion, ultramarine, and one or more iron earth pigments. Small amounts of carbon, and chalk were also identified. Unidentified pigments/materials that may also be present include one or more organic colorants (likely red), and possibly a copper-containing pigment.
